(Assignment 1 Algorithm Explanation) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(1. Most Frequent Registrant) Tj
T*
(A dictionary stores how many times each student ID appears. While scanning the list, the) Tj
T*
(algorithm updates the current most frequent ID whenever a higher count is found. If the) Tj
T*
(input list is empty, it returns None.) Tj
T*
(Worst-case time complexity: O\(n\)) Tj
T*
(Worst-case space complexity: O\(n\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(2. Ordered Deduplication) Tj
T*
(A set tracks IDs that have already appeared, and a result list stores only the first) Tj
T*
(occurrence of each ID. This preserves the original first-appearance order.) Tj
T*
(Worst-case time complexity: O\(n\)) Tj
T*
(Worst-case space complexity: O\(n\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(3. First Unique Student) Tj
T*
(The list is scanned once to count all student IDs, then scanned again to return the first ID) Tj
T*
(whose count is exactly one. If no such ID exists, it returns None.) Tj
T*
(Worst-case time complexity: O\(n\)) Tj
T*
(Worst-case space complexity: O\(n\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(4. Contiguous Subarray Sum) Tj
T*
(The algorithm uses prefix sums. If current_sum - target has appeared before, then the values) Tj
T*
(between the previous prefix and the current position sum to the target.) Tj
T*
(Worst-case time complexity: O\(n\)) Tj
T*
(Worst-case space complexity: O\(n\)) Tj
T*
ET
endstream
