(Assignment 2: University Helpdesk Ticket Queue) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The linked list program defines a Ticket node containing ticket_id, student_name, issue, and) Tj
T*
(next. The TicketQueue class stores head and tail references.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Implemented Operations) Tj
T*
(1. Enqueue Ticket: adds a ticket to the end of the queue. A tail pointer makes this O\(1\).) Tj
T*
(2. Priority Insert: searches for a specified ticket ID and inserts a new ticket immediately) Tj
T*
(after it.) Tj
T*
(3. Resolve Ticket: removes a ticket with the given ticket ID, including correct handling for) Tj
T*
(head, tail, empty queue, and missing ticket cases.) Tj
T*
(4. Find Middle Ticket: uses slow and fast pointers to find the middle ticket in one) Tj
T*
(traversal.) Tj
T*
(5. Reverse Queue: reverses the queue in place by changing next pointers without copying node) Tj
T*
(data.) Tj
T*
(6. Display Queue: traverses and prints each ticket's ID, student name, and issue.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The file includes assertion-based tests for empty queues, single-ticket queues, priority) Tj
T*
(insertion, deletion, middle finding, and reversal.) Tj
T*
ET
